<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>in the whole • on the whole</xh5><p> <i>in the whole</i>—(also: as a whole) considered in its entirety; in full: Council may approve the budget in part or <u>in the whole</u>.</p><p><i>on the whole—</i>1. in general; from every point of view: They think Stalin maybe made a few mistakes but was <u>on the whole</u> a great guy. 2. for the most part: National Health surgeons <u>on the whole</u> remain disinclined to abort frivolously.</p> </entry>
